 The Anambra State Police Command has declared 12 persons wanted for engaging in conducts likely to cause breach of public peace at Isu-Aniocha in Awka North Local Government Area of the state. The names of the wanted persons are given as Edward Okoye, aka Stone, Donatus Okeke, Onyemazi Ngini, Onyebuchi Okoye, Nonso Eboh and Chukwuka Onyibor. Others are Chukwujekwu Anaekeokwu, Chika Ilodigwe, Chinedu Okoye, Nonso Obinna Cosmos Okonkwo and Chukwujekwu Okoye. Among others, they were also declared wanted for alleged conspiracy, armed robbery, terrorism, kidnapping, and cultism, unlawful possession of firearms, house breaking, burglary, and malicious damage. The Force Public Relations Officer, CSP Olumuyiwa Adejobi, in a statement issued on Friday in Abuja, said that Edward Okoye, in conjunction with others shot two men Ifeanyi Anazoba (a.k.a Ichafu) and Chukwuebuka Amodo (a.k.a Mutum) dead on January 19, 2019 at a burial in Umuzuocha town in Awka South Local Government Area of the state. The statement read that the victims were beheaded and burnt beyond recognition. The wanted men were also said to have kidnapped two other person and vandalised property valued at more than N1.2 billion. The statement added that the wanted persons also attacked and brutalised some mobile police officers detailed to restore calm to the community. According to it, the wanted persons, all male of Igbo extraction from Isu-Aniocha, are between 25 and 55 years old. (NAN). 